# shadcn/ui UI Components

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for ALL UI elements — no exceptions. **Zero custom UI components may be created.** Never use raw HTML elements, custom CSS components, or third-party component libraries. If a shadcn/ui component exists for a use case, it MUST be used.

## ABSOLUTE RULES — Never Violate

- **NEVER** create custom UI components from scratch. Every interactive or visual element must come from shadcn/ui.
- **NEVER** use raw HTML elements (`<button>`, `<input>`, `<select>`, `<dialog>`, `<card>`, etc.) — always use the shadcn/ui equivalent.
- **NEVER** install or use other UI libraries (MUI, Ant Design, Chakra UI, Radix UI directly, Headless UI, etc.).
- **NEVER** write custom className-based styled components as substitutes for shadcn/ui components.

## Setup

If shadcn/ui is not yet initialized in the project, run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding Components

If a required component is not installed, add it before using it:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

Example — adding the Button component:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Components are installed into `src/components/ui/`.

## Usage Rules

- **Always** use shadcn/ui components for every piece of UI — buttons, inputs, dialogs, cards, forms, dropdowns, toasts, etc.
- **Always** install the shadcn/ui component first if it isn't already available in `src/components/ui/`.
- Import components from `@/components/ui/<component>`.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

<Button variant="outline">Click me</Button>

// ❌ BAD
<button className="...">Click me</button>
```
